metadata.title: Heart of Innocence unformat
metadata.sourceFile: Jessica Simpson - Heart of Innocence unformat.ttml

lines.text: Sometimes I wake up in the dark night
And in my mind, there's a picture of you
I know someday this dream will come alive
So for now your shadow will do
But I know you're in my heart
I'll hold you in my arms
I have a gift for you
From all that I hold inside
I lay my head down on a pillow of white
Here in the dark, I am cradled in peace
No loss from yesterday to harm me at night
No tears to dry, no sad memories
The strength that's in my soul
I have a gift for you
Waiting for your sweet caress, oh
From all that I hold inside
Every night, I make a wish before I fall asleep
That destiny will take your hand
And lead you to me, oh
(I have a gift for you something I've held on to)
You know I'll be waiting here for you
